reviewText: I have a library of Alvin and the Chipmunk CD's/DVD's and try to get them as soon as they come out around Christmas time.  Sorry, but this one didn't compare to the others.  This was a bummer for my family.

I admit I was disapointed It's ok but I have  several of these befor & I bought them in the last 3 years.
Daves getting married is a very cute episode  but was on their thanksgiving DVD.  now I have it twice.
Every chipmunk tells a story and Maids in Japan are both in the Alviiin DVD  since I lost that DVD  I was glad to have them back but  would have appriciated something new more  I think Romancing Miss Stone was  in the  Alviiiin DVD too.

shrinking dave & Mothers day were 1s I'd never seen & very good  but still 2 out of 6?
What about that great 1 when alvin looses his trademark hat & can't go onstage without it?  It's kinda nice to see his vulnerable and insecure side.

No original title cards are on the episodes... "Maids in Japan" was edited when Alvin Simon and Theodore tried to escape the cab when Dave takes them back to the hotel. That scene is not in this DVD edition. The editing and changes need to stop! The fans should have the right to see the shows in their original Presantation...  From what I have seen in terms of the latest releases, it seems that Peramount and Bagdasarian Productions are going around in circles... I think a disclamer should be put on the package letting customers know if the show has been altered in any way...
It's still great after all of these years.  Fun to watch with my 3 year old.
so cute

This was a cute and funny video.  My son is a spongebob fanatic and has now became hooked on Alvin and the Chipmunks.  This is a nice addition to his new collection of Alvin and the Chipmunks dvds.

I thought the product was absolutely wonderful.  It gave me an opportunity to remember my childhood when the "Alvin and the Chipmunks" TV show was shown more frequently.  I constantly laughed during the episodes.  If you like the old school "Alvin and the Chipmunks" and their ability to provide humor, you should definitely purchase this DVD set.  I could tell on the episodes that the boys really did not want Dave to get married.  I don't want to spoil it for future viewers.  Really loved the item!
